docs.lead_paragraph: The Cortes assembled on the 2d inst. The Duke DR. SALDANHA informed the House that the dispute respecting the General Armstrong claims--which was referred to the Arbitrator of the French Republic, has been decided in favor of Portugal.

headline.main: LATER FROM SOUTH AMERICA.; ARRIVAL OF THE UNITED STATES. Affairs on the Isthmus.

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship United States, Capt. BERRY, arrived at 4 o'clock Saturday morning from Aspin wall on the 19th inst., and Kingston on the 22d. The health of Aspinwall was very good. The Isthmus continued in good traveling order.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Boston Journal, of Thursday, announces the death of the Rev. SYLVANUS JUDD, as having occurred at Augusta, Me., the day previous. Mr. JUDD was the pastor of the Unitarian congregation in that city. His novels, " Margaret, a Tale of the Real and Ideal," Richard Edney," and "Philo," have secured for him the highest repute as a writer of philosophical romance.

headline.main: MORAL AND RELIGIOUS.; Church and Miscellaneous Intelligence.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Union Prayer-meetings which were largely attended in this City, a few months since, have been resumed at Hope Chapel. A service of half an hour is held every morning at 8 1/2 o'clock. The different Evangelical denominations combine in the work.

docs.lead_paragraph: AFFECTING BEREAVEMENT.--An Industrious Irishman, residing in Boston, had accumulated an saved money enough from his earnings, to secure an, furnish a snug little tenement, and to send for his family to come over and occupy it. They took passage in the ship Moses Wheeler, which arrived last week, after stormy and tedious voyage, having been long and anxiously expected.

headline.main: HAVANA.; The Cunningham Case--Cuban Justice--Result of the Boylan Matter.

docs.lead_paragraph: One of the cases which, perhaps, illustrates as forcibly as any other the justice with which Mr. GALIANO may claim the violation of the laws of hospitality, by those who sojourn temporarily in this land, appears in the case of CUNNINGHAM, who was employed as an engineer upon the rail road between this city and Matanzas; and the route particularly, making the connection with the last city.
